# GitHub REST API walkthrough for the GitPulse project
# Uses VS Code REST Client dotenv syntax for the token:
#   @token = {{$dotenv GITHUB_TOKEN}}
# Place this .http file next to your .env file.
#
# Repo defaults match the project README:
#   owner = apache
#   repo  = airflow
#   main-api-url = https://api.github.com 
#


@baseUrl = https://api.github.com
@owner = apache
@repo = airflow
@token = {{$dotenv GITHUB_TOKEN}}

# Replace this after you run one of the list-issues requests below.
@issue_number = 1

# Useful for demonstrating incremental ingestion.
@since = 2026-01-01T00:00:00Z

### 0) Optional: verify auth + show rate limits
GET {{baseUrl}}/rate_limit
Accept: application/vnd.github+json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
X-GitHub-Api-Version: 2022-11-28

### 1) Repository overview
GET {{baseUrl}}/repos/{{owner}}/{{repo}}
Accept: application/vnd.github+json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
X-GitHub-Api-Version: 2022-11-28

### 2) Core endpoint: list issues (page 1)
GET {{baseUrl}}/repos/{{owner}}/{{repo}}/issues?state=all&sort=updated&direction=desc&per_page=5&page=1
Accept: application/vnd.github+json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
X-GitHub-Api-Version: 2022-11-28

### 3) Same endpoint again: page 2
GET {{baseUrl}}/repos/{{owner}}/{{repo}}/issues?state=all&sort=updated&direction=desc&per_page=5&page=2
Accept: application/vnd.github+json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
X-GitHub-Api-Version: 2022-11-28

### 4) Incremental pull example using `since`
GET {{baseUrl}}/repos/{{owner}}/{{repo}}/issues?state=all&sort=updated&direction=asc&since={{since}}&per_page=5&page=1
Accept: application/vnd.github+json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
X-GitHub-Api-Version: 2022-11-28

### 5) Deep dive: one issue
GET {{baseUrl}}/repos/{{owner}}/{{repo}}/issues/{{issue_number}}
Accept: application/vnd.github+json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
X-GitHub-Api-Version: 2022-11-28

### 6) Labels attached to one issue
GET {{baseUrl}}/repos/{{owner}}/{{repo}}/issues/{{issue_number}}/labels
Accept: application/vnd.github+json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
X-GitHub-Api-Version: 2022-11-28

### 7) Optional: repository label catalogue
GET {{baseUrl}}/repos/{{owner}}/{{repo}}/labels?per_page=20&page=1
Accept: application/vnd.github+json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
X-GitHub-Api-Version: 2022-11-28

### 8) Optional: list assignable users for the repo
GET {{baseUrl}}/repos/{{owner}}/{{repo}}/assignees?per_page=20&page=1
Accept: application/vnd.github+json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
X-GitHub-Api-Version: 2022-11-28

### 9) Optional: timeline events for one issue
GET {{baseUrl}}/repos/{{owner}}/{{repo}}/issues/{{issue_number}}/timeline?per_page=50&page=1
Accept: application/vnd.github+json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
X-GitHub-Api-Version: 2022-11-28

### 10) Optional: repository-wide issue events
GET {{baseUrl}}/repos/{{owner}}/{{repo}}/issues/events?per_page=10&page=1
Accept: application/vnd.github+json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
X-GitHub-Api-Version: 2022-11-28

### 11) Optional: only open issues
GET {{baseUrl}}/repos/{{owner}}/{{repo}}/issues?state=open&sort=created&direction=desc&per_page=10&page=1
Accept: application/vnd.github+json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
X-GitHub-Api-Version: 2022-11-28

### 12) Optional: only closed issues
GET {{baseUrl}}/repos/{{owner}}/{{repo}}/issues?state=closed&sort=updated&direction=desc&per_page=10&page=1
Accept: application/vnd.github+json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
X-GitHub-Api-Version: 2022-11-28
